---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
const title = "Reinvestment Scorecard";
---

<BaseLayout title={title}>
  <h1>The Reinvestment Scorecard</h1>

  <section>
    <h2>Purpose</h2>
    <p>
      The Reinvestment Scorecard answers: <strong>“Are resource rents being converted into future-proof assets?”</strong>
      It aggregates five key metrics to assess if a company or country is truly reinvesting for long-term sustainability, rather than extracting and distributing at the expense of future generations.
    </p>

    <h2>Scorecard Metrics & Thresholds</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Metric</th>
          <th>High</th>
          <th>Moderate</th>
          <th>Low</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Sustainable CapEx Share</strong> (renewables, circular economy, etc.)</td>
          <td>&gt; 30%</td>
          <td>10–30%</td>
          <td>&lt; 10%<sup>[1]</sup></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Reserve-Replacement Ratio</strong></td>
          <td>&gt; 120%</td>
          <td>80–120%</td>
          <td>&lt; 80%<sup>[2]</sup></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Reinvestment Rate</strong> (CapEx / OCF)</td>
          <td>&gt; 100%</td>
          <td>50–100%</td>
          <td>&lt; 50%<sup>[3]</sup></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Carbon-transition Progress</strong></td>
          <td>Net-zero ≤ 2040, Scope-3 plan</td>
          <td>Net-zero 2050</td>
          <td>No credible plan<sup>[4]</sup></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Social & Human Capital Spend</strong></td>
          <td>Rising, impact-based</td>
          <td>Stable</td>
          <td>Falling</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h2>Case Snapshot</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Freeport-McMoRan: Scored <strong>Low</strong> on diversification (&lt;5% green CapEx).</li>
      <li>Anglo American: Scored <strong>High</strong> on reserve replacement (Quellaveco copper).</li>
      <li>Ørsted: Scored <strong>High</strong> across the board after exiting fossil fuels.<sup>[5]</sup></li>
    </ul>

    <blockquote>
      Firms that rank <strong>Low</strong> are effectively “eating the seed corn” and would face a <strong>larger user-cost deduction</strong> in sustainable accounts.<sup>[6]</sup>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Interactive Chart</h2>
    <p>
      Use the interactive chart below to explore Freeport, Anglo, and Ørsted’s <strong>Reinvestment-Rate Index (2013 = 100)</strong>.
    </p>
