    <h2>Equations & Calculation Approach</h2>
    <h3>1. Reinvestment Rate</h3>
    <pre>
Reinvestment Rate = (Total CapEx) / (Operating Cash Flow)
    </pre>
    <h3>2. Reserve-Replacement Ratio</h3>
    <pre>
Reserve-Replacement Ratio = (New Reserves Added) / (Production)
    </pre>
    <h3>3. Sustainable CapEx Share</h3>
    <pre>
Sustainable CapEx Share = (Green CapEx + Circular Economy CapEx) / (Total CapEx)
    </pre>

    <h2>Academic Contribution</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        The Reinvestment Scorecard operationalizes the “seed corn” principle from user cost theory, providing a transparent, standardized method to evaluate whether companies are truly reinvesting for the long term.
      </li>
      <li>
        Enables benchmarking across peers, countries, and time periods—pushing both investors and policymakers to prioritize sustainable reinvestment.
      </li>
      <li>
        Fills a major gap in sustainability reporting, which often lacks robust, comparable reinvestment metrics.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>References</h2>
    <ol>
      <li id="ref-1">See paper, Table 1: Sustainable CapEx Share thresholds and empirical data.</li>
      <li id="ref-2">Reserve Replacement Ratio methodology per industry best practice; see Section 3.4.</li>
      <li id="ref-3">CapEx/OCF benchmarks based on leading extractives; see case analysis.</li>
      <li id="ref-4">Net-zero planning criteria: see ESG disclosure standards.</li>
      <li id="ref-5">Company reports and UCA case studies, 2013–2022.</li>
      <li id="ref-6">Original paper: user cost deduction implications for poor reinvestors.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
